Class List<E>

craterdog.collections.List<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of element managed by the collection.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Composite<Sequence<E>>, Sequential<E>, Comparable<Sequence<E>>, Iterable<E>
public class List<E> extends SortableCollection<E>
This collection class implements a sortable list which performs very well for both inserts and indexed lookups of its values. The implementation dynamically scales up and down the size of the underlying data structures as the number of associations changes over time. The indexing is unit based and allows positive indexes starting at the beginning of the collection or negative indexes starting at the end of the collection as follows: 
         1             2             3               N
    [element 1] . [element 2] . [element 3] ... [element N]
        -N          -(N-1)        -(N-2)            -1
Author:
Derk Norton
